        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Map of eastern Tanzania, showing the known distribution of Nothobranchius nikiforovi (blue and red filled diamonds for blue and red phenotypes, respectively) and N. eggersi (blue and red filled circles for blue and red phenotypes, respectively). Individual symbols on the map may represent more than one locality or population where the sites are close to one another and could not reasonably be resolved at the scale of the map. T, type locality; P, site of specimens included in paratypes. Map prepared by B.R. Watters." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4643474/files/figure.png" .

